Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.42,0:15:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The council president.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.09,0:15:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.14,0:15:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I thought he was Rikuyama all along.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.76,0:15:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So that means that Kugayama was the illustrator for Anshin'in Takuha?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.77,0:15:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,"Anshin'in"? What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.11,0:15:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You read that as "Ajimu". It's a place in Kyuushuu.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.57,0:15:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that really something I can't live without knowing?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.41,0:15:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, the reading is written here in small Latin letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.54,0:15:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.83,0:15:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Kugayama did the illustrations, but the story is by Anjou Haruna.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.83,0:15:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You know about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.30,0:15:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I love that manga!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.84,0:15:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I bought it at last's year's culture fair!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.22,0:15:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Wow, Ibara just straight out said she loved it...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.47,0:15:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Oreki, can I have that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.35,0:16:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure you can, but wait a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.64,0:16:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm still using it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.35,0:16:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You're using it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.60,0:16:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh right! I managed to get some airtime on the Radio Club's lunchtime program!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.23,0:16:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.19,0:16:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That's amazing, Chi!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.11,0:16:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Not bad! That's wonderful news!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.49,0:16:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Now selling all the copies of  {\i1}Hyouka{\i0} might be more than just a dream!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.04,0:16:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll teach you the basics of how to speak on air.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.54,0:16:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.96,0:16:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Firstly, your time is limited to about five minutes.{these two lines don't overlap but the conversation switches to background here, so might as well begin the an8 at this point}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.46,0:16:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}So it all depends on how much you can impress people in that short time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.46,0:16:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Ah, I see.{overlaps from here on}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.51,0:16:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The Kan'ya Fair Guide...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.43,0:16:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Secondly, you must make the Classics Club famous!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.97,0:16:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The Gardening Club... The Cooking Club... The Light Music Club...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.89,0:16:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Okay! Leave it to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.81,0:16:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}A very famous Christie novel... Kudryavka's Order...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.18,0:16:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}I'll be counting on you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.40,0:16:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.11,0:16:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,How is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.23,0:16:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.61,0:16:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.37,0:17:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.79,0:17:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm close to a conclusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.62,0:17:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'll need to talk to them about it, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.96,0:17:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Chitanda is in the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.63,0:17:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If she found out what I'm about to do, she'd be against it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.05,0:17:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Satoshi, could you come with me for a moment?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.39,0:17:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So you really did figure something out, Houtarou?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.02,0:17:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, Oreki?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.85,0:17:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Know when to keep your mouth shut, goddamn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.81,0:17:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You see that light in Chitanda's eyes?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.40,0:17:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you notice something?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.40,0:17:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,No! Nothing at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.11,0:17:39.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it's not about the Juumoji incident?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.53,0:17:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.42,0:17:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Oreki...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.42,0:17:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I've... I've been thinking about it all this time, so why did you only ask Fukube...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.01,0:18:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I shouldn't take this any further.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.93,0:18:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it's about the Juumoji incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.81,0:18:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Then please let us know too—
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.69,0:18:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,However, it's quite a dirty story. You okay with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.45,0:18:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So what's this "dirty story" of yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.41,0:18:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry for dragging you out here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.54,0:18:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I don't mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.54,0:18:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not like I have some grand idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.08,0:18:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,There's just a few things that don't fit the big picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.09,0:18:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that means something.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.88,0:18:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Was there some hidden connection between the clubs that got hit?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.63,0:18:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that's not it either.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.18,0:18:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Then what? Did the mysterious thief Juumoji make some fatal mistake?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.52,0:18:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That isn't it either.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.19,0:18:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.86,0:18:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's neither?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.78,0:18:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,There are over a thousand suspects.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.78,0:19:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Were you planning to find the culprit without a connection or a mistake on their part?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.91,0:19:05.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Kinda.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.20,0:19:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,How?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.75,0:19:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know about the culprit yet. I just want to sum up my thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.30,0:19:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's hear it. I expect great things of you, Houtarou.{irisu student #01?}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.77,0:19:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,First: Why would Juumoji steal ten items from ten clubs?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.61,0:19:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just what we theorised he'd do, based on his name.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.57,0:19:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And that theory isn't holding steady either.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.20,0:19:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Second: Why did they leave greeting cards behind at the scene of the crime?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.24,0:19:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,This, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.99,0:19:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Third: Why do they use the word "lost"? It'd be more natural to say that they'd "taken" it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.87,0:19:54.38,signs,,0,0,0,,{\fnDK Crayon Crumble\fs180\blur1.2\c&H4B4C4C&\pos(633,371)}lost
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.84,0:19:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Fourth: Why do they leave the Kan'ya Fair guide behind?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.84,0:20:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not the only thing with a list of clubs in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.63,0:20:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So why are they sticking just to that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.34,0:20:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got one too, by the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.76,0:20:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I picked it up after the cooking competition.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.64,0:20:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Fifth: Why the Gardening Club and the Cooking Club?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.89,0:20:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,There are other clubs that start with the same sound in Japanese.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.65,0:20:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Especially the Cooking Club.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.40,0:20:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not even common to write it in that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.94,0:20:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And that leads us to whether the Classics Club or the Artisan Club will be targeted.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.78,0:20:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Sixth, and this is the weirdest: Why did they skip "ku" and go straight for "ke"?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.45,0:20:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,That's was to elude watchful eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.08,0:20:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You couldn't steal a speck of dust from the Global Action Club without someone noticing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.25,0:20:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Seventh: this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.67,0:20:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That manga has nothing to do with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.47,0:20:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That might not be true.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.55,0:20:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Satoshi, what are Christie's most famous works?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.80,0:20:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see... {\i1}And Then There Were None{\i0}, {\i1}Murder on the Orient Express{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.52,0:20:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The Murder of Roger Ackroyd{\i0}, and {\i1}The ABC Murders{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.02,0:20:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Those four, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.52,0:21:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,If they came up with a retelling of one of those stories called {\i1}Kudryavka's Order{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.40,0:21:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,it'd most likely be based off the ABC Murders.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.70,0:21:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Kudryavka was a dog that was sent into space in a test launch and never returned alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.62,0:21:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't that imply {\i1}And Then There Were None{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.04,0:21:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,This is still just a theory, so it's okay if we don't agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.30,0:21:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I understand what you're trying to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.64,0:21:31.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Satoshi, are they selling a manga titled {\i1}Kudryavka's Order{\i0} at this fair?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.02,0:21:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Nope, I heard nothing like that at from General Affairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.69,0:21:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And if the Manga Lab had something to do with it, Mayaka would've mentioned it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.48,0:21:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.19,0:21:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,They published {\i1}Dead at Dusk{\i0} at last year's fair.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.95,0:21:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,In the afterword, it said they'd publish a manga this year based on a famous Christie novel with "a few twists".
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.83,0:21:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That novel is probably either {\i1}And Then There Were None{\i0} or {\i1}The ABC Murders{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.63,0:22:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And then this year, there's a series of incidents clearly inspired by {\i1}The ABC Murders{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.05,0:22:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that a coincidence?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.93,0:22:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So you say that the Juumoji incident was originally announced in {\i1}Dead at Dusk{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.60,0:22:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't imagine they're not connected at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.98,0:22:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I even feel like Juumoji is trying not to cause too much trouble or
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.03,0:22:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,disrupt the fair's events too much during their chain of thefts.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.12,0:22:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't feel like they're just doing it for the thrill of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.91,0:22:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But then why did they skip "ku"?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.24,0:22:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,They had plenty of ways to pull it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.96,0:22:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Satoshi, this incident has some meaning to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.92,0:22:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going back.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.63,0:22:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a bit worried about Chitanda too.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.55,0:22:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You're right. I'll leave that to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.55,0:22:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll have a look through the stuff you gave me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.89,0:22:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Satoshi!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.06,0:23:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell Chitanda to get something ready that starts with "ko".
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.65,0:23:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Bait for the culprit, right? I thought about that one already.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.98,0:23:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll get some copy papers{proofread manuscript papers}.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.79,0:23:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm counting on you, Houtarou.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.96,0:23:28.84,signs,,0,0,0,,{\c&HCBCBCC&\fs95\blur1\fnArial Rounded MT\pos(640,186)\b1}On air
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.84,0:23:29.59,signs,,0,0,0,,{\c&HBFECFB&\fs95\blur1\fnArial Rounded MT\pos(640,186)\b1}On air
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.30,0:23:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll be going on air at the cue.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.93,0:23:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Five seconds. Four.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.94,0:23:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You're listening to Yoshino Yasukuni's Radio Beat special!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.98,0:23:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning to you all!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.49,0:23:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the one and only Yoshino Yasukuni, comin' at you live!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.03,0:23:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,My guest today on the last day of the fair is the president of the Classics Club,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.91,0:23:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Chitanda Eru from first year class A!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.37,0:24:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.87,0:24:02.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{ED}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.10,0:24:21.80,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,300)}The situation is unscientific
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.76,0:24:25.77,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,0)}A montage of emotions
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.77,0:24:28.35,ED,,0,0,0,,Who's calling who?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.35,0:24:32.56,ED,,0,0,0,,You look away when our eyes are about to meet
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.56,0:24:34.40,ED top,,0,0,0,,I can feel it
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.40,0:24:36.65,ED,,0,0,0,,Am I just imagining things? It's so cold of you
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.65,0:24:42.20,ED,,0,0,0,,It takes talent to read minds
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.20,0:24:43.37,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,250)}You know
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.07,0:24:44.70,ED top,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}You know
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.16,0:24:46.12,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I wanna know
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.91,0:24:47.74,ED top,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.16,0:24:56.88,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,300)}I'll fix the fire of youth in your heart while I can
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.96,0:24:58.71,ED top,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,300)}If we can do it today why leave it for tomorrow
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.71,0:25:04.30,ED,,0,0,0,,I want to solve your mystery
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.30,0:25:09.60,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,300)}Look for the back of the boy, burdened with secrets
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.02,0:25:10.68,ED top,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Even today
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.98,0:25:15.27,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,0)}You are a fantasy and I'm drawn to you
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.27,0:25:19.44,ED,,0,0,0,,This growing curiosity
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.44,0:25:22.24,ED,,0,0,0,,There's no twist in the story
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.24,0:25:23.66,ED,,0,0,0,,I can't stop thinking about it
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.66,0:25:26.66,ED,,0,0,0,,It's so interesting
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.66,0:25:29.20,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,350)}But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.58,0:25:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time: Kudryavka's Order.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.01,0:25:39.85,next episode,,0,0,0,,{\fs60\fad(192,0)\blur1.3\c&HFFFFF8&\pos(640,270)}Kudryavka's Order
